# Core Rules — pixelAI (imaginify)

## Session start

Read `AGENT.md` in the project root before taking any action in a new session. It contains the full project overview, folder structure, key files, and critical agent instructions.

## Clarification

Ask one clarifying question before acting on any ambiguous task. Do not silently assume intent.

## Commit format

Use Conventional Commits for all commit messages:
- `feat:` — new feature or capability
- `fix:` — bug fix
- `refactor:` — code restructure without behavior change
- `chore:` — tooling, deps, config
- `docs:` — documentation only

## Diff discipline

Keep changes minimal and focused. One concern per change. Do not refactor unrelated code while fixing a bug, and do not fix bugs while adding features.

## Path alias

Always use the `@/` alias for imports. It resolves to the project root. There is no `src/` directory.

```ts
// ✅
import { db } from "@/lib/db";
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

// ❌
import { db } from "../../lib/db";
```

## Error handling

Use `handleError()` from `@/lib/utils.ts` inside all `catch` blocks. Never swallow errors silently. Never throw raw errors from Server Actions to the client.

```ts
// ✅
} catch (error) {
  handleError(error);
}

// ❌
} catch (e) {}
```

## No console.log in production code

Remove all `console.log` statements before committing. Use `handleError()` for caught errors.

## No secrets in source

Never hardcode API keys, secrets, tokens, or credentials in any source file. All secrets live in `.env.local`.

## Protected files — do not modify without explicit instruction

- `.env`, `.env.local`, `.env.*`
- `auth.ts`
- `middleware.ts`
- `routes.ts`
- `prisma/schema.prisma`

## Database access

Always use `db` from `@/lib/db.ts`. Never instantiate `PrismaClient` directly. Never use the `mongoose` package — it is an unused dependency.

```ts
// ✅
import { db } from "@/lib/db";
const user = await db.user.findUnique({ where: { id } });

// ❌
import { PrismaClient } from "@prisma/client";
const prisma = new PrismaClient();
```

## Credits

Never mutate `User.creditBalance` directly. Always call `updateCredits()` from `@/data/user.ts`.

## Route protection

Never add a route to `publicRoutes` in `routes.ts` without an explicit user instruction. Never bypass the auth check in `middleware.ts`.
